{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52ee8fd2-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2711"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2711"},"text":"§ 2711.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Application for warrant","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A United States attorney or assistant United States attorney or a person authorized by the Attorney General—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52ee8fd3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2711/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" upon his own affidavit or that of another credible person, stating the existence of either of the grounds of attachments enumerated in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2710"},"text":"section 2710 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52ee8fd4-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2711/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" upon production of legal evidence of the debt","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"may apply for a warrant of attachment to a judge, or, in his absence, to the clerk of any court of the United States having original jurisdiction of the cause of action.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52ee8fd5-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/682/s9"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–682, § 9","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1960-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1960","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/74/707"},"text":"74 Stat. 707","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52ee8fd6-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52ee8fd7-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id52ee8fd8-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was derived from R.S. § 925, which was originally classified to section 738 of former Title 28. Following the general revision and enactment of Title 28 by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1948","children":[],"tail":", R.S. § 925 was reclassified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t39/s838"},"text":"section 838 of Title 39","children":[],"tail":". R.S. § 925 was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/682/s12/c"},"text":"section 12(c) of Pub. L. 86–682","children":[],"tail":" (section 1 of which revised and enacted Title 39), and reenacted by section 9 thereof as "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s2711"},"text":"section 2711 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52ee8fd9-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id52ee8fda-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"t